<TITLE>Tax revenue lags in Gold Rock</TITLE>
<TEXT>
The target of ongoing narcotics and prostitution investigations Gold Rock motels collect significantly less tourism taxes than other Rocky Mount hotels The Gold Rock area at Interstate 95 and N C 48 is rife with criminal activity attracting the attention of Nash County authorities who want to shut down the seedier establishments with nuisance abatement lawsuits and start over A bump in the road is that in 1997 the Rocky Mount City Council satellite annexed the small area made up of motels a handful of gas stations a couple of diners and an ABC store City officials have their own plans for improving the downtrodden area Once a bright spot for tourism Gold Rock has slipped further and further from the sun in the last few decades The Nash County Travel and Tourism Development Authority collects 5 percent of every hotel room sale in the county including the nine motels at Gold Rock the eight hotels around Winstead Avenue the 10 hotels along U S 301 and 10 other inns scattered around the county Records obtained by the Telegram show overall Rocky Mount hotel room sales have increased in recent years while sales at Gold Rock have declined In 2002 03 total sales was at 21 8 million climbing to 28 million in 2015 16 At Gold Rock motel room sales dropped from 5 5 million in 2002 03 to 3 4 million in 2015 16 dipping below 3 million for five of those years The numbers show expanding sales for hotels along Winstead Avenue and U S 301 but a steady decline for the motels at Gold Rock In fiscal year 2015 16 the Winstead Avenue hotels collected 947 520 93 That same year the motels at Gold Rock collected 176 772 89 Or to put it another way Winstead Avenue hotels took in 69 51 percent of the occupancy tax collected while Gold Rock motels collected 12 97 percent Of course rooms at Gold Rock are cheaper with some of the motels advertising 25 a night but the real reason the motels aren t filling up is folks are uncomfortable staying there according to county officials In 2016 there were nearly 100 arrests made or incident reports filed related to the Gold Rock area by the Rocky Mount Police Department Calls for service were much higher At one motel alone Rocky Mount Police responded to 137 calls including assaults domestic violence mental person suicide suspicious persons trespassing and a weapons call according to a report prepared by the Rocky Mount Police Department Crime Analysis Unit Crime has become so common in Gold Rock that the tourism authority recommends out of town visitors avoid the area with the exception of two motels said Nash County board Chairman Robbie Davis who also heads the tourism authority When we have a soccer tournament and all the other hotels in Rocky Mount are full we send families to Roanoke Rapid or Wilson even Goldsboro but not Gold Rock Davis said 
